text:
Heads up BD team, that for our Node operators, we should still expect that they have the DA Utility installed and up-to-date on their nodes. The Attestor code and our smart contracts will use parts of it. They just don’t need to use the UI for Credentials anymore. 

I noticed in some chats you telling them they don’t need it, so please keep in mind. 

For regular holders/minters, we technically don’t need it right now, but until there are Token Standard wallets on Canton, the Utility will be the only place they can see/interact with CBTC Holdings.

So it’s safest to just tell them to have the Utility ready. Just not for Credentials.
